,Recommended,299720,32205508,Posted: 5 June,all,MAriskaDeville,"https://youtu.be/SL8K7GjeO04An interesting take on the tower defense genre. Yes the tower types are nothing new, and the graphics and sound are fairly sparse and simplistic. But don't let that put you off.The core idea in this TD game is to construct 'platforms' to mount your turrets to, and to maximise thier arcs of fire. You also have several targetting options to specify what the turrets should target. Combined with the map layouts, turns terrorhedron into a pretty complex game, much deeper than you usually find in this genre.This game can get pretty tough and challenging, and if you like TD then I deffo recommend giving this one a try for the low cost."
