,Not Recommended,299720,17164057,"Posted: 21 July, 2015",all,Zero,"The game lacks polish.For example, the game features an unlock system, where you have to play the game more before you unlock the different tower types.  On the one hand, I suppose this system is intended to ease players into the game.  I would have preferred having everything to toy around with at the beginning; right now I'm playing the game just to unlock the types before I really start playing around with it.However, the isn't implemented into the UI well.  Locked tower types are greyed out before you've unlocked them.  The problem is that all unlocked towers stay highlighted, even when you don't have enough money to buy them.  I frequently try to buy towers when I don't have enough money, assume that I bought them, and look back to see they're not there.  There's no ""you can't buy this"" error noise, no flashing X over the button... just nothing.It would have been nice to have the prices of the towers shown above the icons rather than only display on hovering over the icon.  It would also be nice to have your total money shown on the bottom of the screen next to the ""buy"" icons so that you can see more easily how much money you have left.Also, when placing the towers, hovering over a tower placement spot should ghost the tower in and show its range.  I keep placing towers and expecting them to have their range 10-15% bigger.  It keeps feeling like tower placement spots *should* just reach a little bit longer, but they fall short fairly often.Additionally, towers can't shoot at anything below their placement plane.  I was expecting the towers to be able to shoot downward within a ~30 degree angle; most tower placement spots are absolutely useless because they can't shoot at ANYTHING below the horizontal plane they're placed in....and there's no resolution options, or framerate options.  And there's no options to turn up the shadow quality.  And there's no button in the pause screen to restart the level.  There really also could have been a way to go back to the beginning of the last wave....and there's no way to change the controls.  And the game should zoom in more for each click of the scroll wheel.  And the game should zoom in toward where the mouse is focused on the screen.  And I have a brother who only plays games with controller support.I was wondering if this game was actually released or not.  A bunch of these ought to have been fixed in an Early Access phase.  But the game has been out for a year, and it's apparently not getting any better than this.Just get Defense Grid instead."
