,Recommended,299720,19508586,"Posted: 5 December, 2015",all,thedawesome,"TLDR:8/10 Great tower defense gameFull Review:Terrorhedron takes the traditional tower defense formula and adds a twist by having the game utilize three dimensions rather than the traditional two. This is an interesting change to the tower defense formula and adds a new layer of strategy. The other main difference Terrorhedron adds is the ability to build connector blocks to tower locations, meaning you can turn a single tower slot into a defensive megastructure.The music is great and really adds to the minimalist tech feel that the game provides. The enemies are all colored shapes which change depending on how many hits they can take. Towers are unlocked throughout play at a reasonable pace, I never really felt like I was grinding for a new tower or being given too many options too quickly. You can also upgrade your towers which generally provides them with a new ability rather than just a stat boost, which is great.I can't think of any real problems with this game. I have been having a ton of fun with Terrorhedron and if you are a fan of tower defense games I think you would too."
,Recommended,299720,19452157,"Posted: 2 December, 2015",all,Shawnecy,"A geometric TD game. The unique twists here are two: 1) though you have a limited number of spots upon which you can build towers, you can build structures that add more platforms for building. 2) The stage twists into three dimensions as does the platform building. This allows for some pretty cool and unique strategies.The graphics are nothing special but are fitting. Same can be said for the music. The controls are a tiny bit wonky, but nothing that really hurts gameplay. Though I believe it offers no advanced features like multi-select or such.I'm personally not a huge TD fan, but I dug this one a bit. I'd recommend this for anyone who finds at least the more popular TD games interesting.7/10"
