,Recommended,299720,18335921,"Posted: 4 October, 2015",all,Chesture,"I am going to preface this review with a single statement: I despise the tower defense genre with all of my being and would not hesitate to damn the vast majority of tower defense games to the bowels of Hell, if such a thing were possible.That being said, I love this game.I picked this game up for $0.24 cents and would not hesitate to pay full price. I played for about 20 minutes and instantly fell in love. It vastly differs from other games of its kind. Whereas with typical tower defense games you have a grid or pretermined locations where you can place towers, and those towers sit there and do their thing, this game instead gives you base platforms on which you can build. You are able to construct almost tree-like structures covered in towers which you can use to obliterate your tiny foes as they attempt to progress along the little track to which they are bound. The simple graphics, chiptune music, and sheer uniqueness in the gameplay make this a great game in my opinion.10/10 would build laser trees again."
